!!!
%html
  %head
    %meta{:charset => "utf-8"}/
    %title jQuery Mobile Docs - Lists
    %link{:href => "../../themes/default/", :rel => "stylesheet"}/
    %link{:href => "../_assets/css/jqm-docs.css", :rel => "stylesheet"}/
    %script{:src => "../../js/jquery.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../../js/", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../docs/docs.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
  %body
    %div{"data-role" => "page"}
      %div{"data-role" => "header", "data-theme" => "b"}
        %h1 Theming lists
        %a.ui-btn-right.jqm-home{"data-direction" => "reverse", "data-icon" => "home", "data-iconpos" => "notext", :href => "../../"} Home
      / /header
      .ui-body{"data-role" => "content"}
        %p All the standard button swatches can be applied to lists. The framework assigns a default list theme swatch of &quot;c&quot; (silver in the default theme) and swatch &quot;b&quot; (blue in default theme) for dividers. Below is a default themed list.
        %code
          \&lt;ul data-role=&quot;listview&quot; data-inset=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
        %ul{"data-inset" => "true", "data-role" => "listview"}
          %li{"data-role" => "list-divider"} Divider
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Inbox
            %span.ui-li-count 12
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Outbox
            %span.ui-li-count 0
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Sent
            %span.ui-li-count 328
        %h2 Theming list items
        %p
          The list item color scheme can be changed to any button color theme swatch by adding the
          %code data-theme
          attribute to the list, and setting the letter theme swatch. Here is the same list above with the &quot;a&quot; swatch applied.
        %code
          \&lt;ul data-role=&quot;listview&quot; data-inset=&quot;true&quot; data-theme=&quot;d&quot;&gt;
        %ul{"data-inset" => "true", "data-role" => "listview", "data-theme" => "d"}
          %li{"data-role" => "list-divider"} Divider
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Inbox
            %span.ui-li-count 12
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Outbox
            %span.ui-li-count 0
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Sent
            %span.ui-li-count 328
        %p Data-theme attributes also work at the LI-level, for styling a single item.
        %ul{"data-inset" => "true", "data-role" => "listview", "data-theme" => "d"}
          %li{"data-role" => "list-divider"} Divider
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Inbox
            %span.ui-li-count 12
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Outbox
            %span.ui-li-count 0
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Sent
            %span.ui-li-count 328
          %li{"data-theme" => "a"}
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Trash
            %span.ui-li-count 34
        %h2 Theming dividers
        %p
          The theme for
          %strong list dividers
          can be set by adding the
          %code data-dividertheme
          to the list and specifying a swatch letter. Here is an example of the same list above with swatch &quot;d&quot; set on the dividers.
        %code
          \&lt;ul data-role=&quot;listview&quot; data-inset=&quot;true&quot; data-theme=&quot;d&quot; data-dividertheme=&quot;c&quot;&gt;
        %ul{"data-dividertheme" => "c", "data-inset" => "true", "data-role" => "listview", "data-theme" => "d"}
          %li{"data-role" => "list-divider"} Divider
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Inbox
            %span.ui-li-count 12
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Outbox
            %span.ui-li-count 0
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Sent
            %span.ui-li-count 328
        %h2 Theming count bubbles
        %p
          The theme for
          %strong count bubbles
          can be set by adding the
          %code data-counttheme
          to the list and specifying a swatch letter. Here is an example with swatch &quot;e&quot; set on the dividers.
        %code
          \&lt;ul data-role=&quot;listview&quot; data-inset=&quot;true&quot; data-theme=&quot;a&quot; data-dividertheme=&quot;d&quot; data-counttheme=&quot;e&quot;&gt;
        %ul{"data-counttheme" => "e", "data-dividertheme" => "d", "data-inset" => "true", "data-role" => "listview", "data-theme" => "a"}
          %li{"data-role" => "list-divider"} Divider
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Inbox
            %span.ui-li-count 12
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Outbox
            %span.ui-li-count 0
          %li
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Sent
            %span.ui-li-count 328
        %h2 Theming icons
        %p
          The default icon for each list item is
          = succeed "." do
            %code arrow-r
          To override this, set the
          %code data-icon
          attribute on the desired list item to the
          = succeed "." do
            %a{:href => "../buttons/buttons-icons.html"} name of a standard icon
          To prevent icons from appearing altogether, set the
          %code data-icon
          attribute to &quot;false&quot;.
        %pre
          %code
            :preserve
              
              &lt;li data-icon=&quot;info&quot;&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Notices&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
              &lt;li data-icon=&quot;alert&quot;&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Alerts&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
              &lt;li data-icon=&quot;false&quot;&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;All Notifications&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        %ul{"data-icon" => "false", "data-inset" => "true", "data-role" => "listview"}
          %li{"data-role" => "list-divider"} Divider
          %li{"data-icon" => "info"}
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Notices
          %li{"data-icon" => "alert"}
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Alerts
          %li{"data-icon" => "false"}
            %a{:href => "index.html"} All Notifications
        %h2 Theming split buttons
        %p For split lists which a second button, the framework default to &quot;b&quot; for the theme swatch (blue in the default theme)  Here is a default split list:
        %ul{"data-inset" => "true", "data-role" => "listview"}
          %li
            %img{:src => "images/album-bb.jpg"}/
            %h3
              %a{:href => "index.html"} Broken Bells
            %p Broken Bells
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Purchase album
          %li
            %img{:src => "images/album-hc.jpg"}/
            %h3
              %a{:href => "index.html"} Warning
            %p Hot Chip
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Purchase album
        %code
          \&lt;ul data-role=&quot;listview&quot; data-inset=&quot;true&quot; data-splittheme=&quot;a&quot;&gt;
        %p
          To specify the color swatch for the icon button on the right, add the
          %code data-splittheme
          to the list and specify a swatch letter. This attribute can also be added to individual split inside list items by adding a
          %code data-theme
          attribute to specific links  (see second list item).
        %ul{"data-inset" => "true", "data-role" => "listview", "data-splittheme" => "a"}
          %li
            %img{:src => "images/album-bb.jpg"}/
            %h3
              %a{:href => "index.html"} Broken Bells
            %p Broken Bells
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Purchase album
          %li
            %img{:src => "images/album-hc.jpg"}/
            %h3
              %a{:href => "index.html"} Warning
            %p Hot Chip
            %a{"data-theme" => "e", :href => "index.html"} Purchase album
        %p
          The icon for the split theme can set at the list level by adding the
          %code data-spliticon
          to the list and specifying a
          = succeed "." do
            %a{:href => "../buttons/buttons-icons.html"} standard icon
          This attribute can also be added to individual split inside list items by adding a
          %code data-icon
          attribute to specific links (see second list item).
        %code
          \&lt;ul data-role=&quot;listview&quot; data-inset=&quot;true&quot; data-splittheme=&quot;a&quot; data-spliticon=&quot;plus&quot;&gt;
        %ul{"data-inset" => "true", "data-role" => "listview", "data-spliticon" => "plus", "data-splittheme" => "a"}
          %li
            %img{:src => "images/album-bb.jpg"}/
            %h3
              %a{:href => "index.html"} Broken Bells
            %p Broken Bells
            %a{:href => "index.html"} Purchase album
          %li
            %img{:src => "images/album-hc.jpg"}/
            %h3
              %a{:href => "index.html"} Warning
            %p Hot Chip
            %a{"data-icon" => "delete", "data-theme" => "e", :href => "index.html"} Purchase album
